**_About Sirma Solutions:_**  
Sirma Solutions, part of Sirma Group Holding JSC, is a market leader in
Software Development, IT Consulting Services and System Integration. Founded
in 1992, Sirma Solutions delivers complex and cutting-edge projects worldwide
for clients from different business verticals.  

**_Job purpose:_**

The Technical Project Manager is responsible for managing teams of between 2
and 8 developers and QA engineers. The position reports to the Director of
Technology Services and is based in Sofia. Internally the company uses a
DevOps process based on the Atlassian stack – including but not limited to
Jira, Confluence, Bamboo and Git/BitBucket. Projects are required to perform
continuous integration and continuous test and we typically maintain separate
test, QA, staging and production environments for each project. The majority
of our deployments are on the Amazon AWS platform. We use many of the advanced
AWS services and features. We use a branch-by-feature and commit-with-code-
review methodology. Some client projects are configured for continuous
delivery.  
The Technical Project Manager will manage projects that employ modern Web
application tools. Specifically, the Web Applications group of the company is
focused on the Meteor/node.js/io.js and mongoDB as a preferred platform.
Projects also use a combination of Grunt/Gulp, less/Sass, Angular/React and
other tools and frameworks as necessary or required by client projects.  
Out server-side stacks are typically Java or .NET based. While not a primary
focus, we do work on and support applications based on PHP, python or other
technologies.  
We implement telephony and call center systems based on Asterisk and open
source PHP web apps.  
We also work in C, C++, bash and python on Linux platforms and embedded
devices.  
We use a mix of desktop Windows, OS X, Linux and VMware platforms and Windows,
Ubuntu, CentOS and Kali Linux server distributions. Projects are typically
deployed on either Amazon AWS, Microsoft Azure or our own Daticum data center
cloud platforms.  
The Technical Project Manager will be required, as part of day-to-day
responsibilities, to select one of a set of company-specified open source
projects and time is allocated in order to make contributions on a monthly
basis.

**_Key__ Responsibilities:_**

  * Timely delivery of working systems that meet customer needs;
  * Support new client efforts with project planning;
  * Plan, organize and supervise project execution of outsourcing projects;
  * Responsible for daily project management, ensuring project progress visibility;
  * Coordinate team efforts with client counterparts and internal stakeholders;
  * Manage project scope and expectations of Negotiate schedule / scope / quality tradeoffs in a transparent fashion;
  * Make sure that development process and approach of clients meets project needs;
  * Coordinate and execute release deployment;
  * Provide the necessary Project Metrics (e.g. Effort to date, Estimated Cost to Complete, Estimated effort at Completion);
  * Contribution to company processes, standards and methodologies;
  * Set standards with clients for Issue Tracking system management and other development process systems and processes;
  * Assure proper project documentation maintenance, write and manage specification

**_Requirements:_**

  * Bachelor/Master of Science in Computer Science, Computer Engineering;
  * Excellent spoken and written English;
  * Ability to communicate effectively in writing as well as in person and to build and motivate a small team;
  * Excellent understanding of Software Development methodology and management techniques from waterfall to agile;
  * Ability to communicate with clients and prospective customers and present themselves in a professional and competent manner;
  * Ability to manage own time effectively, prioritize and meet tight deadlines;
  * Willingness to learn new things and self-confidence to ask questions about anything;
  * Excellent problem solving, communication, and interpersonal skills;
  * Experience working with virtual teams;
  * Experience in one traditional programming language – C, C++, C#/.NET or Java is considered as plus;

**_Why Sirma Solutions should be your choice:_**

  * Top salary, catchy perks and other social benefits;
  * Exciting working environment, friendly chaps and experience exchange with colleagues around the world;
  * Travel around clock and opportunity to visit cool places;
  * Team buildings and sport opportunities;
  * Personal development program that appraises people for their strengths, achievements and problem solving skills;
  * Work-life balanceand flexible schedule.

If you feel interested and challenged by this position and if you meet or even
excel the given criteria, we will be glad to hear from you and to further
discuss your professional aspirations.

All applications will be dealt strictly confidentially. Only short-listed
candidates will be contacted.

